This license covers the project files for this Polytoria world, which have
been made open source. Alongside giving credit, a goal of this license is to
make it easy for people who come across this project or its remixes to find
their way back to the original GitHub repository.

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy
of this software and associated files (the "Project") to use, copy, modify,
merge, remix, publish, and distribute the Project, including for creating
your own worlds or builds based on it, subject to the following condition:

You must give reasonable credit to the original author, qtepi, by doing
at least one of the following:

(a) If you are creating your own open source project based on the Project
(e.g. publishing your own fork or derivative repository), keep this
licence file included with the Project files, and include a link to
the original GitHub repository: 
https://github.com/riceareseeds/qtepi-s-experimental-cars. This option
is only available to open source projects; or

(b) Credit "qtepi" somewhere a player or visitor would naturally see it —
for example, in the world's description, an in-game credits/about
area, or a loading/menu screen. A link to the GitHub repository above
is a bonus here, but not required — the credit itself is what
matters; or

(c) If the Project (or your remix or build of it) is used as a Polytoria
world, place credit for "qtepi" in that world's description.

You only need to satisfy one of (a), (b), or (c) — not all three. The goal
is simply that people encountering your version can find out the original
was made by qtepi, and can easily find the original GitHub project if they
want to — it doesn't need to be prominent or formal.

